**Scope and assets**

**Primary assets**

*   **Customer Profile**: Policy holder & dependent details (PII: name, DOB, phone, email, address).
*   **Policy Data**: Applications, approval/rejection decisions, active policies, policy cover, premium.
*   **Claims Data**: Claim submissions, statuses, reasons, approved amounts, cheque data.
*   **Credentials**: Policy holder, agent, staff, admin accounts.
*   **Medical Documents (PHI)**: Age proofs, medical diagnostic reports, hospital bills.

**Secondary assets**

*   **Audit logs**: Auth events, lock/unlock, application/claim state changes, cheque entries, document events.
*   **Configuration**: Premium rules (age bands, discounts), rejection reasons, doc allowlist (types/size), rate limits.
*   **Reports**: Operational dashboards, reconciliation/audit exports.
*   **Session tokens**: JWTs/refresh tokens, signed URLs for documents.
*   **Installer/environment**: .env, seed users, migrations, default security settings.

**Users**

*   **Policy holders** (internet)
*   **Agents** (internet)
*   **Company staff** (intranet: underwriting, claims, finance)
*   **Administrators** (intranet: IAM/config)
*   **Auditors** (optional; read-only)
*   **Attackers (external)**
*   **Malicious insiders**

**Trust boundaries**

*   **Client ↔ Web server**: Browser SPA to API Gateway/BFF over **TLS**.
*   **Web server ↔ App services**: Auth, Policy, Claim, Document, Notification services over secure internal network (mTLS optional).
*   **Company portal (Intranet)**: Elevated access with stricter controls, IP allowlisting/network segmentation.
*   **Document storage**: Encrypted object storage; access via **time-limited signed URLs** only.
*   **Batch jobs**: Nightly archival, audit exports, config refresh; run as separate **service accounts** with least privilege.

**Authentication and Login**

**User Registration / Provisioning**

*   Collect **only necessary details** (holder: name, email, phone, DOB; agent/staff: official email/role).
*   Validate inputs **server-side**; never trust client-only validation.
*   Store passwords using hashing with salt (**bcrypt**/Argon2).
*   **Policy holder credentials** are issued **after policy approval** (activation link or temp password).
*   Agents/Staff/Admin provisioned by Admin; intranet SSO (optional, future-ready).

**Login**

*   **Username + password** as primary login for all roles.
*   **Step-up verification (optional)** for **sensitive actions** (e.g., entering cheque details, approving high-value claims).
*   After **3 failed attempts → lock account**. Unlock **only by Admin** (intranet) with audit log.

**Password Rules**

*   Minimum **10 characters**, include letters, numbers, symbols.
*   **Prevent reuse of last 3 passwords**.
*   **Forgot Password**: secure reset link/SMS OTP, expires in **15 minutes**, single-use.

**Session Management**

**Session Tokens**

*   Internet portals: **JWT access** (≤ 15 min) + **refresh token** (≤ 7 days).
*   Intranet: JWT or secure server-sessions (cookies).

**Cookie & Security Flags**

*   Mark cookies **Secure** and **HttpOnly**.
*   Use **SameSite=Strict** (or Lax where flows require).
*   Enforce **HTTPS** and **HSTS**.

**Session Timeout**

*   **Auto logout after 15 minutes** of inactivity.
*   **Absolute expiry** after **8 hours** even if active.

**Session Renewal**

*   Regenerate session ID after login and after privilege elevation (e.g., entering Admin area).
*   Invalidate access & refresh tokens on logout.

**Concurrent Sessions**

*   Option to **allow only one active session per user** (stricter posture).
*   Notify user on **new device/location** login.

**Authorization and roles**

**Role-based access control (RBAC)**

| Role | Key permissions | Constraints |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Policy Holder | View personal details; view policy details; view claim statuses | Read-only; own resources only; masked PII where appropriate |
| Agent | Create policy applications; add members; upload documents; submit claims; view status | Access limited to their customers; strict server-side validation |
| Company Staff | Approve/Reject policy applications; Approve/Reject claims; enter cheque details; view documents | Intranet only; enhanced audit; optional dual control for high-risk actions |
| Admin | Unlock accounts; manage roles; manage premium/config tables | Intranet only; dual control for config changes; change management required |
| Auditor (optional) | Read-only access to logs/reports | Immutable log access; no data modification |

**Implementation notes**

*   **Policy-based authorization**: Enforce fine-grained policies (e.g., OwnsResource, CanApprovePolicy, CanEnterCheque, CanViewMedicalDoc) at the service layer.
*   **Resource scoping**: Use **opaque identifiers**; enforce **server-side ownership checks**; never rely on client-supplied IDs.
*   **Dual control (recommended)**: Require two distinct Staff/Admin approvals for **sensitive changes** (e.g., premium rule updates, cheque entries over threshold, force status override).
*   **Least privilege**: Separate service accounts for batch jobs and per-service DB access; default-deny network and APIs.
*   **Rate limiting**: Apply stricter throttles to login and document upload endpoints.
*   **Document security** (PHI):
    *   Allowed types: pdf, jpg, jpeg, png; **max size configurable** (e.g., 10 MB/file).
    *   **Mandatory AV scan** on upload; quarantine on fail; block submission.
    *   Store in **encrypted object storage**; access only through **signed URLs** with short TTL (≤ 5 minutes).
    *   Apply **RBAC + ownership** before issuing signed URL; **audit** every issue/download event.
    *   Clarify policy on whether **holders/agents can download** medical docs (default: restricted; staff full access).
*   **Audit logging**: Capture login success/failure, lock/unlock, submit/approve/reject (policy/claim), document upload/quarantine/link-issue, cheque entry (metadata only). Retain ≥ 1 year.
*   **Input/Output safety**: Server-side DTO validation, parameterized queries/ORM, output encoding, **CSP** headers, standardized error responses (no stack traces or secrets).
*   **Secrets & config**: No secrets in code; use environment variables or vault; rotate keys/tokens; secure defaults in installer.
